### Demographics {#Sec11}

We compared the demographics of patients reporting anxiety/depression with those who did not report these conditions. We observed that patients who reported anxiety/depression were older (mean age 56.7 vs 54.3 years; *P* = .012), female (77.4% vs 69.0%; *P* = .004) and had more severe RA (moderate, 40.0% vs 22.1%; severe, 7.9% vs 1.3%; *P* \< .001) with longer disease duration (mean 8.7 vs 6.7 years; *P* \< .001). These patients also experienced more severe pain (mean score 4.1 vs 2.8; *P* \< .001) on a scale of 1 to 10.

