Other shuffles like pshufd or psrldq would work, but punpckhqdq gets the job done without needing an immediate byte, so it's one byte shorter. SSSE3 palignr could get the high element from one register and the low element from another register into one vector, but tehy'd be reversed (so we'd need a pshufd to swap high and low halves).

