The payload resource exists – I'm able to access it directly via browser. Using the syntax prescribed by the Twilio PHP helper library client returns a 61005 "Bad request" error:
 $request = $client->v1->lookups
 ->phoneNumbers("+1XXXXXXXXXX")
 ->fetch(
 array(
 "AddOns" => "ibm_watson_speechtotext",
 ));

Using cURL to get the resource directly has been equally unfruitful, returning an empty string. $request = json_decode($_REQUEST['AddOns']);
